The code works in the way:
first i used the opencv code. It detects the face with green rectangle using casccade classifier.
Then the next logic is to publish if face is detected.
this is done by:
--> first connecting to the mqtt client
--> our brokker is test.mosquito and port is 1883
--> we first connect the publisher to the ip and the port
--> after this, we put the opencv code..
--> just after face is detected, publish a message saying that face is detected.
--> we also print this message in our terminal
--> close the live streaming using destroy all windows and cap.release.
--> then close the mqtt connection.

the subsriber works in the same way as it would do in mqtt:
--> connect to the broker
--> subscribe to an topic. 
--> Using the on_message function decode the message.
-->subscriber runs in an infinite loop.